main event: A radar sighting of an unidentified flying object over Iwo Jima on 24 July 1952 lasting approximately 15 to 30 seconds.
interesting points: The object was tracked visually and via radar,The sighting was made by military personnel,Only one object was reported during the sighting,The object's course was from west to east,No photographs or physical evidence were collected during the observation.
witness description: military personnel involved in radar operations
